This paper is about improving the energy efficiency of deep convolutional neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also introduces a new approach to designing sparse convolutional layers, which could be of interest to researchers in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses the trade-off between energy consumption and accuracy, which is a topic that could be relevant to researchers in data science (cs.DS).
